<item>
            <title>[WFCORE-1919] CLI client freezes for removed management realm</title>
                <link>https://issues.jboss.org/browse/WFCORE-1919</link>
                <project id="12315422" key="WFCORE">WildFly Core</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Steps to Reproduce:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;./standalone.sh&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;./jboss-cli.sh -c&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;/core-service=management/security-realm=ManagementRealm/authentication=local:remove&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;reload&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;lt;Ctrl+C&amp;gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;


&lt;p&gt;The client is already connected, Management realm is removed, client is reloaded. &lt;br/&gt;
The user is prompted for UserName (local-auth has been disabled).&lt;br/&gt;
Ctrl-C is typed.&lt;br/&gt;
During Ctrl-C handling, the client is closed although it is &quot;reconnecting&quot; and has kept a lock. This lock is required to close the client. Lock that will never been released.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
